body_html:
I closed it because I was referring to TF 1.9 but the documentation I linked above reffers to the master branch. Anyway I tried the nightly build as well and it still doesn't work (so I'm reopening the issue now). I am currently trying to do this via a frozen graph (.pb) file and will report my findings.

Update
The frozen graph file can also not be converted. The error is:

F tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/graph_transformations/resolve_tensorflow_switch.cc:95] Check failed: other_op->type == OperatorType::kMerge \nAborted (core dumped)\n'
None

I used the transform_graph tool with the strip_unused_nodes flag beforehand.

body:
I closed it because I was referring to TF 1.9 but the documentation I linked above reffers to the master branch. Anyway I tried the nightly build as well and it still doesn't work (so I'm reopening the issue now). I am currently trying to do this via a frozen graph (.pb) file and will report my findings.

**Update**
The frozen graph file can also not be converted. The error is: 

> F tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/graph_transformations/resolve_tensorflow_switch.cc:95] Check failed: other_op->type == OperatorType::kMerge \nAborted (core dumped)\n'
> None

I used the transform_graph tool with the strip_unused_nodes flag beforehand.
